      "text": "<h2 style=\"font-family:times\">THE TAKE-AWAY: Develop a range of personas that capture important user types/conditions. Base them in real-life as far as you can. Personalise them to a rather strong degree - particularly do this in terms that are not directly related to the specific use-case - give them personalities, more than job-titles.</h2> \n<h3  style=\"font-family:times\">Give these personas real names ('Jane Designer, 'Maggie Manager\"), ages, gender, family background, education, income, character - enough to make them feel like a person. </h3>\n<h3  style=\"font-family:times\">Don't be afraid of stereotyping - it is inevitable. But at the same time be aware of it - make sure that your personas aren't drawn so narrowly from real-life that you risk enshrining some accident of social history into your design.</h3>"
